Q:What happens when you initialize a repository?Why do you need to do it?
A:.git file created in repository. We need to do it to make it trackable.

Q:How is the staging area different from the working directory and the repository? what value do you think it
offers?
A:Staging area is the place were files are kept to be commit. change in the file will not reflect in this files, which
are been add for commit. It gives us place were we can keep file for commit. before commit, we can change the files which 
we want ot commit.


